docs.snippet: WASHINGTON, July 12. -- Although the total dollar value of our exports increased in May over a year ago, shipments to the great markets of Europe, Northern North America and South America all declined, an analysis by the Commerce Department showed...
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, July 12. -- Although the total dollar value of our exports increased in May over a year ago, shipments to the great markets of Europe, Northern North America and South America all declined, an analysis by the Commerce Department showed today.

headline.main: SALES TO EUROPE DECLINED IN MAY; Exports to South America Also Fell, Despite Rise in Total Dollar Value.

byline.original: Special to THE NEW YORK TIMES

docs.snippet: Criticism directed at the mark deals by which Germany acquired large quantities of coffee and other "cash" crops of Latin-American republics has resulted in action which will put a permanent end to such transactions in at least three countries,...
docs.lead_paragraph: Criticism directed at the mark deals by which Germany acquired large quantities of coffee and other "cash" crops of Latin-American republics has resulted in action which will put a permanent end to such transactions in at least three countries, according to information received here by interested exporters last week.
docs.abstract: Sale of coffee and other products to German buyers who tender registered marks banned

headline.main: REICH MARK DEALS WILL BE OUTLAWED; Action to Stop 'Compensation' Purchases Has Been Taken by at Least 3 Countries.
